HEADWORD: Hydroscope
<hw>Hy"dro*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An instrument designed to mark the presence of water, especially in
air.</def> <rj><au>Weale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of water clock, used anciently for measuring
time, the water tricking from an orifice at the end of a graduated
tube.</def></p>

<p><ent>Hydrosoma</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hydrosome</ent>⟦br⟧
